 NGOZI OKORIE THE Peoples Democratic Party’s candidate,
Chimaobi Ebisike, has been declared the winner of Saturday’s Aba North and South Federal Constituency bye-election. The Independent National Electoral Commission’s Returning Officer for the constituency, Prof. Fidelis Okpata of the Federal University Ndufu Alike Ikwo, Ebonyi State, announced the results. According to him, Ebisike got.10,322 votes to defeat his closest rival, Mascot Uzor Kalu of the All Progressives Congress candidate, who polled 3,674 votes. The All Progressives Grand Alliance candidate, Destiny Nwagwu, polled 1,554 votes to come distant third; while the Action Alliance candidate; Okey Prestige, got 199 votes. Details later… 